# API & permissions rules

Roles and scoping per `@docs/PR_Pulse_Master_PRD.md` (User Roles section).

## Authentication & roles
- **Google OAuth only** (no passwords). Three roles: `campaign_manager`, `senior_manager`, `admin`.
- **Campaign Manager:** assigned campaigns only (can see peers' work within them); can read all contacts; cannot delete contacts, manage users, or view audit logs.
- **Senior Manager:** all campaigns + team visibility; approves registrations; manages brands; bulk import; blacklist/un-blacklist.
- **Admin:** full access incl. user management, system config, audit logs.

## Query scoping defaults (enforce centrally, not per-endpoint)
- **Contacts are globally readable** (relationship memory). **Engagement management is campaign-scoped.**
- Default list/search scope **excludes `status = 'archived'`** unless explicitly requested.
- **Campaign population excludes `is_blacklisted = true`** by default; force-add must warn.

## Writes
- Open a transaction per mutating request and `SET LOCAL app.current_user_id = '<uuid>'` so audit/timeline attribute correctly.
- Never expose endpoints that bypass the DB completion guard or recompute triggers.

## Reporting
- Client-facing report exports and **shareable links must strip** `agreed_fee`, `internal_rating`, and `internal_notes` (use the `client_visible` flag).
- Shareable links carry an **expiry (default 30 days)** and support **revocation**.
